		"AbilityTooltips"
		{
			"bloodseeker_bloodrage"		"Bloodrage earlier on can be used on yourself to help with your last-hitting and regeneration of life. The cooldown is quite low and costs 0 mana.

In the later levels, you can cast this on the attacker and the target to amplify damage taken/dealt and chance of healing.

Bloodrage amplifies all types of damage taken/dealt."
			"bloodseeker_blood_bath"		"Blood Rite is an incredible nuke that works in combination with your ultimate: Rupture. Open with Rupture then Blood rite to ensure all damage is both taken. Bloodrage should be your follow-up or if you can cast it before Blood Rite pops."
			"bloodseeker_thirst"		"Thirst is your damage output. The longer a fight is going and the more damage dealt to enemies; the faster you attack and move.

Provides True Sight if unit is below 25% health."
			"bloodseeker_rupture"		"Use Rupture to keep opponents' still where you know your team will be able to reach them.

1. Target an enemy with Rupture
2. Activate Bloodrage on yourself
3. Use Blood Rite to nuke and entrap the target

Works on enemies using Black King Bar or are magic immune. Lethal if enemy keeps moving."
